<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>1986</DATELINE><TITLE>A simple, rapid method for preparation of virus isolates from cell culture for electron microscopy</TITLE><BODY>A simple procedure for the rapid preparation of virus isolates from cell culture for negative-contrast electron microscopy was devised. Using only conventional centrifugation steps (i.e. without ultracentrifugation), the procedure produced consistent, fine-quality preparations of a variety of virus types differing in size/shape and buoyant density.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>